  "prompt": "What is the best all round fighter jet as of 2015?",
  "response": "As of 2015, picking the \"best all-around fighter jet\" is a highly debatable topic. It really depends on what you mean by \"best\" and what specific capabilities you prioritize. However, a strong contender for that title in 2015 was the **Lockheed Martin F-22 Raptor**.\n\nHere's why the F-22 was often considered the top choice:\n\n*   **Stealth:** It possessed unmatched stealth capabilities compared to other fighters at the time. This made it extremely difficult to detect and engage, giving it a significant advantage in air-to-air combat.\n*   **Supercruise:** The ability to sustain supersonic speeds without using afterburners gave it a tactical advantage in intercepting targets and maneuvering.\n*   **Sensor Fusion:** Advanced sensor fusion combined data from radar, electronic warfare systems, and other sources to provide the pilot with a comprehensive situational awareness picture.\n*   **Air-to-Air Prowess:** It was designed primarily as an air superiority fighter and excelled in that role, equipped with advanced air-to-air missiles and a highly capable radar.\n*   **Agility:** Despite its size, the F-22 was surprisingly agile.\n\n**However, there were also arguments against the F-22 as the \"best all-around\" fighter:**\n\n*   **High Cost:** The F-22 was extremely expensive to purchase and maintain.\n*   **Limited Air-to-Ground Capability:** While it had air-to-ground capabilities, they weren't as robust as dedicated strike fighters.\n*   **Export Restrictions:** The U.S. government prohibited the export of the F-22, meaning other countries couldn't acquire it.\n*   **Small Fleet Size:** Relatively few F-22s were produced compared to other fighter jets.\n\n**Other notable contenders in 2015 included:**\n\n*   **Boeing F/A-18E/F Super Hornet:** A versatile carrier-based fighter with good air-to-air and air-to-ground capabilities. It was also more affordable and widely available than the F-22.\n*   **Eurofighter Typhoon:** A highly capable European fighter with good maneuverability and advanced avionics.\n*   **Dassault Rafale:** A French multirole fighter known for its agility and sensor suite.\n*   **Sukhoi Su-35:** A Russian air superiority fighter with impressive maneuverability and long-range capabilities.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\nWhile other jets had their strengths, the F-22 Raptor was often considered the most advanced and capable air superiority fighter in 2015, giving it a strong claim to the title of \"best all-around\" fighter jet. However, its high cost and limited availability were significant drawbacks. The best choice ultimately depended on the specific needs and priorities of the user.\n",
